
[1]magnesia

   MAGNE'SIA, n. s as z. [Gr. the lodestone.]

   1. A primitive earth, having for its base a metallic substance, called
   magnesium. It is generally found in combination with other substances.
   It is absorbent and antacid, and moderately cathartic.
